#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "Achieving PCI-DSS Compliance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If credit or debit card data is processed at your site, it can be necessary "
"to follow the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI-DSS). This "
"appendix will help you implement the portions of the standard that relate to "
"the operating system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "PCI-DSS Is Site-specific"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PCI-DSS implementations vary depending on the site. This guide cannot give a "
"general blueprint."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "PCI-DSS Is Not a Purely Technical Standard"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Large parts of PCI-DSS refer to organizational measures which are not a "
"focus of this document. Always review and follow the original documentation "
"provided at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/"
"security_standards/documents.php\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additional Standards for Software Developers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your organisation develops software intended to be PCI-DSS compliant, you "
"could be obliged to additionally follow the PA-DSS standard. This standard "
"is available from <link xlink:href=\"https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/"
"security_standards/documents.php\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first version of PCI-DSS, 1.0, was released in 2004. The current "
"version, 3.0, was released in November 2013 and is valid for the period "
"between January 1, 2014 and December 31, 2016. The PCI-DSS&nbsp;3.0 "
"specification has the following main requirements:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:97 security_pcidss.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build and maintain a secure network and secure systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Protect cardholder data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maintain a vulnerability management program"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Implement access controls"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Monitor and test networks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maintain an information security policy"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is important to know that PCI-DSS divides account data into two "
"categories:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cardholder data which can be stored: Primary Account Number (PAN), "
"cardholder name, expiration date, and the service code."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sensitive authentication data which must not be stored: magnetic stripe data "
"or equivalent, CAV2/CVC2/CVV2/CID, PIN data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "When Your Organization Does Not Need to Be PCI-DSS Compliant"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often organizations use third-party service providers that handle credit "
"card processing for them. If your organization's equipment comes into "
"contact with cardholder names, expiration dates, and service codes, but not "
"with Primary Account Numbers, there could be no need for your organization "
"to implement PCI-DSS. See also the <link xlink:href=\"https://www."
"pcisecuritystandards.org/pdfs/pci_fs_data_storage.pdf\"> PCI-DSS Data "
"Storage Do's and Don'ts </link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Securing Networks and Systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section of the PCI-DSS standard is concerned with enabling, assessing, "
"and maintaining firewall and router configurations. The second part of this "
"section is concerned with default passwords."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "Firewall and Router Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To learn how to set up and maintain a software firewall, see <xref linkend="
"\"cha.security.firewall\"/>. To correctly set up routers and other network "
"equipment, refer to the documentation of its vendor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure to run as few services as possible on your computers. Avoid "
"enabling use of protocols and services that are considered insecure, such as "
"IMAP, POP3, or FTP. To regulate inbound and outbound connections, use a "
"whitelist approach."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Protect all computers that could come in contact with account data. Enable a "
"firewall such as &susefirewall; on company or private laptops or other "
"portable computers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changing Default Passwords and Other Parameters"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ensure that all passwords used for the operating system are changed from the "
"defaults. In this context, it can be helpful to use a centralized "
"authentication system, such as Kerberos. See also <xref linkend=\"cha."
"security.kerberos\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: security_pcidss.xml:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sknorr, 2014-06-24: Is it necessary to delete these users or is disabling "
"them enough?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Disable all users that are not strictly necessary for running a computer. "
"This includes users that system services have automatically generated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_pcidss.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling the user <systemitem>wwwrun</systemitem> in &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user <systemitem>wwwrun</systemitem> is only necessary to run the Apache "
"Web server. Since a computer that stores account data should not need to run "
"a Web server, the user can be disabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open &yast; as the <systemitem>root</systemitem> user:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: security_pcidss.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;sudo -i /sbin/yast"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Security and Users</guimenu> <guimenu>User "
"and Group Management</guimenu></menuchoice> by using the <keycap function="
"\"down\"></keycap> and <keycap function=\"right\"></keycap> arrow keys. Open "
"this item by pressing <keycap function=\"enter\"></keycap>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the filter to <guimenu>System Users</guimenu> by pressing "
"<keycombo><keycap function=\"alt\"></keycap><keycap>S</keycap></keycombo>, "
"<keycombo><keycap function=\"alt\"></keycap><keycap>S</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the entry <systemitem>wwwrun</systemitem> from the list by using the "
"<keycap function=\"down\"></keycap>, <keycap function=\"up\"></keycap>, and "
"<keycap function=\"enter\"></keycap> keys."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable the account, press <keycap function=\"tab\"></keycap> until "
"<guimenu>Disable user login</guimenu> appears selected. Activate the check "
"box by pressing <keycap function=\"enter\"></keycap>. An <literal>x</"
"literal> will now appear."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save the setting by pressing <keycombo><keycap function=\"alt\"></"
"keycap><keycap>O</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "To disable more accounts, repeat the previous three steps."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_pcidss.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you are finished, leave the dialog by pressing <keycombo><keycap "
"function=\"alt\"></keycap><keycap>O</keycap></keycombo> and &yast; by "
"pressing <keycombo><keycap function=\"alt\"></keycap><keycap>Q</keycap></"
"keycombo>."
msgstr ""

